@page "/modules"

<PageTitle>Roadmap | Linux Made Sane</PageTitle>

<div class="page-shell">
    <UiHeroPanel Title="Roadmap" Compact="true" />

    <section class="feature-grid">
        <article class="surface-card module-card active">
            <p class="eyebrow">Now</p>
            <h2>Host inventory + remote access</h2>
            <p>Managed host records, live terminal access, health snapshots, and SFTP browsing.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="surface-card module-card active">
            <p class="eyebrow">Now</p>
            <h2>LinuxMadeSane.Shares</h2>
            <p>Visual Samba management, permission explanation, effective access checks, guided presets, issue scanning, and mount helper flows.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="surface-card module-card active">
            <p class="eyebrow">Now</p>
            <h2>LinuxMadeSane.Services</h2>
            <p>Systemd helper, sane updater, and repair flows for drift, broken deploys, restart loops, and active-but-bad service states.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="surface-card module-card active">
            <p class="eyebrow">Now</p>
            <h2>LinuxMadeSane.AI</h2>
            <p>Persistent AI chat threads, server attachment, trust profiles, approval records, tool invocation history, checkpoints, and audit logging foundations.</p>
        </article>

        <article class="surface-card module-card">
            <p class="eyebrow">Next</p>
            <h2>Command runs + fleet tasks</h2>
            <p>Structured remote task execution across single hosts and multi-host groups, with sudo-aware workflows and audit-friendly output capture.</p>
        </article>
    </section>
</div>
